298
00:28:40,533 --> 00:28:42,133
<i>I'll draw it for you again.</i>

299
00:28:44,834 --> 00:28:47,567
<i>If you forget this,
you can't find your way back home.</i>

300
00:28:50,700 --> 00:28:52,900
<i>Even if you lose me,</i>

301
00:28:52,967 --> 00:28:55,734
<i>you can find your way back
if you memorize this.</i>

302
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:56,800
<i>Okay?</i>

303
00:29:53,533 --> 00:29:55,900
<i>This is the tricky part.</i>

304
00:29:55,967 --> 00:29:59,567
<i>Some may say that you can't dunk
a ball and can't make it to the NBA,</i>

305
00:29:59,633 --> 00:30:02,367
<i>but you're considered good
in your neighborhood.</i>

306
00:30:02,433 --> 00:30:04,467
<i>Considering that you didn't do anything...</i>

307
00:30:04,533 --> 00:30:05,734
<i>It makes sense.</i>

308
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:08,567
<i>This is the famous controversy
on human nature and nurture.</i>

309
00:30:08,633 --> 00:30:09,467
<i>I see.</i>

310
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:11,533
{\an8}YOUNGSHIN STATION
OUR HOUSE

311
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:09,033
Ryeong.

312
00:32:13,667 --> 00:32:15,266
I've missed you.

313
00:32:25,367 --> 00:32:26,467
Me too.

314
00:32:30,433 --> 00:32:32,300
I've missed you, too.

315
00:32:37,166 --> 00:32:39,633
I've missed you so much.

316
00:32:52,433 --> 00:32:53,467
I'm...

317
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:58,300
I'm really sorry.

318
00:33:50,700 --> 00:33:51,533
Mom.

319
00:33:54,667 --> 00:33:56,100
Who are you?

320
00:34:09,934 --> 00:34:11,667
Who are you?

321
00:34:12,867 --> 00:34:13,767
I'm in the wrong...

322
00:34:18,667 --> 00:34:19,533
I'm sorry.

323
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:52,567
My hair looks great today.

324
00:35:13,834 --> 00:35:14,867
Sir.

325
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:18,433
I remember you now.

326
00:35:20,100 --> 00:35:23,033
You once asked me

327
00:35:23,100 --> 00:35:26,133
how old I am, right?

328
00:35:27,633 --> 00:35:29,100
You have great taste.

329
00:35:31,500 --> 00:35:33,600
That's right. I did.

330
00:35:33,667 --> 00:35:35,633
I asked your age
because you were so pretty.

331
00:35:37,900 --> 00:35:38,800
Here we meet again.

332
00:35:39,867 --> 00:35:43,834
Do you have a family member here?

333
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:45,633
Yes.

334
00:35:46,834 --> 00:35:50,900
My mother has dementia,
so she doesn't recognize me.

335
00:35:52,533 --> 00:35:54,734
That must be upsetting.

336
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:56,533
No, I'm not upset at all.

337
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:58,967
My mom...

338
00:36:00,233 --> 00:36:03,867
She seems to be happier
than when she remembered me.

339
00:36:04,767 --> 00:36:07,700
Even so, you must be upset.

340
00:36:09,533 --> 00:36:10,967
No, I'm okay.

341
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:22,567
<i>I feel the most reassured and comforted</i>

342
00:36:23,333 --> 00:36:27,533
<i>when I lean against your chest.</i>

343
00:36:29,500 --> 00:36:33,000
Ever since you were born and until now.

344
00:36:34,967 --> 00:36:36,000
So...

345
00:36:38,333 --> 00:36:41,200
Don't try too hard because of me.

346
00:36:44,533 --> 00:36:47,667
You don't have to do that.

347
00:36:51,066 --> 00:36:51,934
<i>That day,</i>

348
00:36:52,967 --> 00:36:55,867
<i>you did everything you can do for me.</i>

349
00:36:57,567 --> 00:36:59,233
<i>I'm okay now, Mom.</i>

350
00:37:04,200 --> 00:37:05,800
You still look beautiful today.

351
00:37:06,834 --> 00:37:07,667
What?

352
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:11,533
Thank you.

353
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:30,800
We got a special vacation.

354
00:37:31,734 --> 00:37:34,266
We've made it, right?

355
00:37:34,633 --> 00:37:37,533
Of course. We even got an award.

356
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:40,600
What a great view and a nice breeze.

357
00:37:41,133 --> 00:37:43,133
This is a great spot, Rookie.

358
00:37:44,300 --> 00:37:46,767
You see, Jin is a homebody.

359
00:37:47,667 --> 00:37:52,166
She's scared to be in crowded places,
so I brought her here.

360
00:37:53,834 --> 00:37:58,300
But when we were here,
she still had her eyes only on me.

361
00:38:00,100 --> 00:38:01,300
That's when I realized

362
00:38:02,200 --> 00:38:04,600
that I was the one
who made her a homebody.

363
00:38:06,867 --> 00:38:07,800
To be honest,

364
00:38:08,333 --> 00:38:10,533
I'm the one who hates
going to crowded places.

365
00:38:12,367 --> 00:38:16,734
When Jin makes a loud noise,
people try hard not to stare.

366
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:23,033
Since Jin feels everything I feel,

367
00:38:24,133 --> 00:38:25,767
she didn't like crowded places either.

368
00:38:32,233 --> 00:38:35,066
But I don't care about
people staring at us now.

369
00:38:37,200 --> 00:38:41,767
Jin does feel everything that you feel.

370
00:38:42,200 --> 00:38:44,800
Since you're happy,
she's enjoying the flowers.

371
00:38:46,400 --> 00:38:47,467
Wait.

372
00:38:47,533 --> 00:38:50,600
It must've been hard for Jin
to look after her sister.

373
00:38:51,533 --> 00:38:54,467
Oh. You're right.

374
00:38:54,533 --> 00:38:55,934
-I was the problem.
-Gosh.

375
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:56,934
You were.

376
00:38:57,000 --> 00:38:58,333
-Jin.
-Let's go get Jin.

377
00:38:58,400 --> 00:39:00,133
-I'll go get her.
-Okay.

378
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:02,300
-Gosh.
-I'm sorry.

379
00:39:02,367 --> 00:39:03,734
-I'm so tired.
-Jin.

380
00:39:09,600 --> 00:39:10,467
Let's go eat.

381
00:39:22,767 --> 00:39:24,100
Now this is what I call a vacation.

382
00:39:28,533 --> 00:39:30,700
-The water is so clear here.
-Yes.

383
00:39:30,767 --> 00:39:33,033
-Father.
-Hey!

384
00:39:33,100 --> 00:39:34,867
-That's cold.
-It's okay.

385
00:39:34,934 --> 00:39:35,967
Hey.

386
00:39:46,333 --> 00:39:47,734
-It's so clear!
-Hey.

387
00:39:49,533 --> 00:39:50,367
Hey.

388
00:39:50,900 --> 00:39:52,934
-Hey.
-It's so cold.

389
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:54,800
-It's cold.
-Jin.

390
00:39:57,233 --> 00:39:59,066
-It's deeper than I thought.
-Brain freeze.

391
00:39:59,934 --> 00:40:03,333
-There are fish here.
-Hey. Let's go over there, too.

392
00:40:11,033 --> 00:40:13,834
Jin. Su-ho caught some fish.

393
00:40:14,367 --> 00:40:15,467
Would you like to see them?

394
00:40:15,834 --> 00:40:18,600
Be careful.

395
00:40:18,667 --> 00:40:20,000
Careful.

396
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:25,700
-Look. These are fish.
-Fish!

397
00:40:28,700 --> 00:40:29,533
Rookie.

398
00:40:34,767 --> 00:40:36,567
Well...

399
00:40:38,200 --> 00:40:40,400
Did you find a place for Jin?

400
00:40:40,734 --> 00:40:43,433
There is a group home near our place.

401
00:40:43,500 --> 00:40:45,834
-I see.
-People like Jin gather there

402
00:40:45,900 --> 00:40:48,934
to learn how to get along
with others and be independent.

403
00:40:50,567 --> 00:40:53,600
She can stay there overnight
when I'm on night duty.

404
00:40:54,600 --> 00:40:57,266
That's great. I hope she likes it there.

405
00:40:59,734 --> 00:41:00,667
Rookie.

406
00:41:01,700 --> 00:41:03,200
I have something for you.

407
00:41:18,066 --> 00:41:19,834
What is this?

408
00:41:21,066 --> 00:41:21,900
Open it.

409
00:41:31,800 --> 00:41:34,500
YOO JIN

410
00:41:37,967 --> 00:41:39,100
I...

411
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:44,233
I was going to give it to Jin myself,
but she won't give me a glance.

412
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:48,600
Your number is on here, too.

413
00:41:49,967 --> 00:41:51,700
I need to be close enough with Jin

414
00:41:53,400 --> 00:41:56,834
so she can trust me and call me
when something happens to her.

415
00:42:02,100 --> 00:42:03,333
No.

416
00:42:49,934 --> 00:42:52,433
-You're not going to wash up?
-No.

417
00:42:52,500 --> 00:42:53,467
Oh, you won't...

418
00:42:54,300 --> 00:42:55,533
You won't wash up.

419
00:42:56,967 --> 00:43:00,200
You never change.

420
00:43:00,900 --> 00:43:01,767
Right?

421
00:43:02,867 --> 00:43:03,967
It's no use.

422
00:43:07,300 --> 00:43:09,800
Let's go to bed now.

423
00:43:13,367 --> 00:43:14,200
Oh, my.

424
00:43:36,767 --> 00:43:38,367
-Rookie.
-Yes?

425
00:43:46,266 --> 00:43:49,800
The answer that you haven't given me...

426
00:43:51,767 --> 00:43:52,867
I want to hear it now.

427
00:43:56,967 --> 00:44:01,834
To be honest,
I want us to be official right now,

428
00:44:02,567 --> 00:44:04,133
but that would be selfish of me.

429
00:44:05,266 --> 00:44:08,166
So give me your answer after we catch him.

430
00:44:10,800 --> 00:44:12,266
The answer?

431
00:44:13,834 --> 00:44:14,767
Should we...

432
00:44:15,300 --> 00:44:16,133
starting today...

433
00:44:18,500 --> 00:44:20,567
Should we be official starting today...

434
00:44:21,166 --> 00:44:22,033
Okay.

435
00:44:24,667 --> 00:44:25,500
What?

436
00:44:27,166 --> 00:44:28,600
What did you say?

437
00:44:31,133 --> 00:44:34,667
I'll be your girlfriend starting today.

438
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:39,166
Really? I should've asked sooner.

439
00:44:39,233 --> 00:44:41,900
Thank you.
I'll be good to you forever. I mean...

440
00:44:41,967 --> 00:44:43,266
I'll keep being good to you.

441
00:44:48,233 --> 00:44:50,767
-Thank you.
-Thank you more.

442
00:45:12,667 --> 00:45:13,500
Then...

443
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:16,166
Shall we go to bed now?

444
00:45:17,133 --> 00:45:18,700
Good night.

445
00:45:28,533 --> 00:45:29,667
Good night.

446
00:45:34,500 --> 00:45:35,767
It won't close all the way.

447
00:46:28,433 --> 00:46:29,934
STAFF LOUNGE

448
00:46:37,266 --> 00:46:39,867
-Let's go for our morning undercover.
-Gosh.

449
00:46:40,667 --> 00:46:44,633
You sound like
we're going for our morning walk.

450
00:46:45,900 --> 00:46:47,233
You make me feel...

451
00:46:49,300 --> 00:46:50,166
so refreshed.

452
00:47:39,700 --> 00:47:42,500
You may be my boyfriend
but don't get in the way of my job.

453
00:47:42,567 --> 00:47:44,367
Don't cross the line at work.

454
00:47:44,433 --> 00:47:47,667
You beat me to it. Don't cross the line.

455
00:47:47,734 --> 00:47:50,900
You may be my girlfriend,
but I won't forgive you for being rude.

456
00:47:50,967 --> 00:47:53,000
How is a detective going after
a bad guy being rude?

457
00:47:53,066 --> 00:47:54,633
He had a weapon with him.

458
00:47:54,700 --> 00:47:58,033
Why would you go after him unarmed?
I told you to go bring a stun gun.

459
00:47:58,100 --> 00:47:59,567
What if something happened
while I was gone?

460
00:47:59,633 --> 00:48:01,266
What would happen when I was on him?

461
00:48:02,533 --> 00:48:04,000
You don't trust me?

462
00:48:09,467 --> 00:48:10,400
Jeez.

463
00:48:48,500 --> 00:48:51,500
She shot the gun only to save the victim.

464
00:48:52,500 --> 00:48:56,867
Please give us another chance.
I will teach her to be a better detective.

465
00:48:57,367 --> 00:49:00,166
I bought this to give it
to my partner when I got one.

466
00:49:01,033 --> 00:49:03,300
I finally get to give it to you.

467
00:49:06,166 --> 00:49:09,400
Thank you, Partner.

468
00:49:13,200 --> 00:49:17,433
-Let's get started.
-Keep your eyes only on me.

469
00:49:29,066 --> 00:49:30,767
I'm Shinmok Patrol Station's
Officer Yoo Ryeong.

470
00:49:30,834 --> 00:49:32,567
I'm here for the interview.

471
00:49:32,633 --> 00:49:35,500
The thrill I get when the subway
travels 110 km per hour underground.

472
00:49:35,567 --> 00:49:39,700
How great would it be
if I could feel that at work every day?

473
00:49:41,700 --> 00:49:42,767
Is she a pervert?

474
00:49:46,367 --> 00:49:48,233
I'm here.

475
00:49:51,834 --> 00:49:54,734
I thought you were dead.

476
00:50:20,266 --> 00:50:23,266
Don't ever mess
with my partner ever again.

477
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:26,767
I hold a total of 18 dan
in martial arts, too!

478
00:50:39,600 --> 00:50:41,567
I have a cut here, too.

479
00:51:02,867 --> 00:51:05,300
I'll be careful from now on.

480
00:51:06,700 --> 00:51:07,834
Can I trust you this time?

481
00:51:08,700 --> 00:51:11,166
-Trust me.
-I'm telling you.

482
00:51:12,767 --> 00:51:14,767
You'd better not get a cut
on your pretty face.

483
00:51:16,667 --> 00:51:17,934
Look at this. Let me see.

484
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:22,266
-It hurts, right?
-No.

485
00:51:24,734 --> 00:51:25,567
Give me your hand.

486
00:52:24,333 --> 00:52:25,734
You're here early.

487
00:52:28,266 --> 00:52:29,100
Yes.

488
00:52:29,967 --> 00:52:31,333
I got excited since it's our first date.

489
00:52:38,367 --> 00:52:39,767
Where should we go?

490
00:52:40,367 --> 00:52:43,266
Rookie, what do you like to do
besides catching bad guys?

491
00:52:46,567 --> 00:52:47,633
Well...

492
00:52:48,533 --> 00:52:49,467
I...

493
00:52:52,533 --> 00:52:54,567
-I like to stay still and do nothing.
-What?

494
00:52:55,767 --> 00:52:57,934
I thought you couldn't stay still
for a second.

495
00:52:58,000 --> 00:52:59,033
That's exactly why.

496
00:52:59,834 --> 00:53:02,266
I want to do something
that I've never done.

497
00:53:03,300 --> 00:53:04,133
That's nice.

498
00:53:05,000 --> 00:53:06,867
I like staying still
and doing nothing, too.

499
00:53:11,233 --> 00:53:12,200
All right.

500
00:53:12,800 --> 00:53:13,867
Then...

501
00:53:14,834 --> 00:53:17,967
Let's not do anything
and stay still today.

502
00:53:35,867 --> 00:53:37,300
This is nice.

503
00:53:39,567 --> 00:53:41,633
What were you like as a child?

504
00:53:42,500 --> 00:53:44,400
I can imagine you being
a bossy little devil.

505
00:53:46,266 --> 00:53:47,700
I...

506
00:53:48,266 --> 00:53:49,333
I was the chatty one.

507
00:53:49,934 --> 00:53:51,767
Chatty?

508
00:53:52,500 --> 00:53:54,500
You know how class presidents
wrote down names

509
00:53:54,567 --> 00:53:57,333
of the students who were chatty?

510
00:53:57,400 --> 00:53:58,900
My name was always on the list.

511
00:54:01,900 --> 00:54:03,967
-What about you?
-I was...

512
00:54:05,667 --> 00:54:08,433
I was the one writing the names
of the chatty students.

513
00:54:08,500 --> 00:54:09,767
I was a leader back then too.

514
00:54:14,700 --> 00:54:17,200
What did you want to be as a child?

515
00:54:20,800 --> 00:54:21,700
Superman.

516
00:54:22,734 --> 00:54:26,066
It was my dream to catch
even the villains in space.

517
00:54:26,133 --> 00:54:27,433
You were ambitious.

518
00:54:27,500 --> 00:54:31,700
I thought I could fly
if I practiced a bit more.

519
00:54:31,767 --> 00:54:34,934
So I jumped off passionately.

520
00:54:36,033 --> 00:54:36,934
Then what happened?

521
00:54:37,533 --> 00:54:40,100
Well... The result was terrible.

522
00:54:40,166 --> 00:54:43,066
I got scrapes and broken bones.

523
00:54:44,133 --> 00:54:46,867
I managed to put up with you,
thanks to that experience.

524
00:54:48,300 --> 00:54:51,400
Put up with me? You're dramatic.

525
00:54:56,500 --> 00:54:57,467
Gosh.

526
00:54:58,800 --> 00:55:00,467
This feels like someone else's patio.

527
00:55:01,200 --> 00:55:04,166
Someone else's? What do you mean?

528
00:55:04,233 --> 00:55:05,533
Well...

529
00:55:06,567 --> 00:55:08,734
I'm sitting on my patio as usual,

530
00:55:08,800 --> 00:55:12,266
but it feels different
because I'm with you.

531
00:55:14,033 --> 00:55:14,900
So...

532
00:55:15,800 --> 00:55:17,600
Do I make you feel uncomfortable?

533
00:55:17,967 --> 00:55:19,667
That's not what I meant.

534
00:55:20,433 --> 00:55:21,700
It's just that...

535
00:55:23,266 --> 00:55:26,700
I wonder if the sky has always
looked this beautiful from here

536
00:55:27,400 --> 00:55:30,166
and if the neighborhood always
sparkled like this.

537
00:55:33,600 --> 00:55:35,600
That's what I meant.

538
00:55:37,200 --> 00:55:41,033
So you're saying that
even if you're doing nothing,

539
00:55:42,066 --> 00:55:45,300
it's nice because you're with me?

540
00:55:49,266 --> 00:55:52,900
I was getting sick of Wangsuri Station,

541
00:55:54,433 --> 00:55:56,800
but it feels like a different station now.

542
00:55:58,500 --> 00:56:00,600
What kind of nonsense is that?

543
00:57:14,900 --> 00:57:15,834
Captain.

544
00:57:18,333 --> 00:57:19,767
I saw him.

545
00:57:19,834 --> 00:57:22,000
-Who are you talking about?
-Fruit Knife.

546
00:57:22,066 --> 00:57:24,233
I ran after him but lost him
because of the crowd.

547
00:57:24,300 --> 00:57:25,500
Fruit Knife? Are you sure?

548
00:57:25,567 --> 00:57:28,333
We've been after him for so long.
I'm sure it was him.

549
00:57:28,400 --> 00:57:29,266
Who's that?

550
00:57:29,333 --> 00:57:31,200
He's a pickpocket
who carries a fruit knife.

551
00:57:31,266 --> 00:57:32,567
About a year ago,

552
00:57:32,633 --> 00:57:34,233
a drunk passenger woke up and grabbed him,

553
00:57:34,300 --> 00:57:35,667
and he stabbed the guy and ran.

554
00:57:36,767 --> 00:57:39,800
Since then, he's been lying low,
and it became an unresolved case.

555
00:57:40,500 --> 00:57:42,767
Bastard. I'll get him.

556
00:57:42,834 --> 00:57:45,033
But since he used a knife,

557
00:57:45,100 --> 00:57:48,934
he was considered a robber,
so the Violent Crimes Team took the case.

558
00:57:49,000 --> 00:57:49,834
So...

559
00:57:50,867 --> 00:57:53,767
Shouldn't we hand this case
over to the Violent Crimes Team?

560
00:57:57,700 --> 00:58:01,133
We also have the right
to investigate violent crime cases.

561
00:58:02,600 --> 00:58:03,734
Let's investigate ourselves.

562
00:58:05,667 --> 00:58:08,600
We have the right to investigate
and the ability to do so.

563
00:58:10,600 --> 00:58:11,667
We're more than capable.

564
00:58:12,533 --> 00:58:15,600
Then shall we go undercover
starting today?

565
00:58:15,667 --> 00:58:17,500
We'll ride the subway...

566
00:58:20,000 --> 00:58:21,600
from the first train to the last one!

567
00:58:58,533 --> 00:58:59,367
Sir.

568
00:59:03,867 --> 00:59:04,700
Sir.

569
00:59:18,767 --> 00:59:22,333
Fruit Knife. It's been a long time.
You still have the same hairstyle.

570
00:59:22,400 --> 00:59:23,533
Damn it, you...

571
00:59:26,200 --> 00:59:27,133
Hey!

572
00:59:27,200 --> 00:59:29,533
-What's going on here?
-What?

573
00:59:29,600 --> 00:59:32,066
-How long have you been here?
-Three stations before you got on.

574
00:59:32,133 --> 00:59:35,166
Why did you go over to him?
I have so much jewelry on me.

575
00:59:35,233 --> 00:59:36,800
It's because we have the experience.

576
00:59:36,867 --> 00:59:39,300
-He's a serial robber. It's our case.
-Jeez.

577
00:59:39,367 --> 00:59:42,300
We're onto him, too.
I've already cuffed him.

578
00:59:42,367 --> 00:59:44,300
The person to cuff him first
takes the credit.

579
00:59:44,367 --> 00:59:45,400
Good job, Rookie.

580
00:59:45,467 --> 00:59:47,500
-Salute. Let's go.
-Let's go.

581
00:59:47,567 --> 00:59:48,900
-He's ours.
-What do you mean?

582
00:59:48,967 --> 00:59:50,433
-Where are we?
-On the subway.

583
00:59:50,500 --> 00:59:52,200
Then it's our jurisdiction. Let go!

584
00:59:52,266 --> 00:59:54,200
-Let go!
-Don't hold back, Rookie.

585
00:59:54,266 --> 00:59:55,200
Hey!

586
00:59:56,367 --> 00:59:57,767
Let go.

587
00:59:58,367 --> 00:59:59,834
-You little...
-It's ours!

588
00:59:59,900 --> 01:00:01,166
Let go.

589
01:00:01,233 --> 01:00:02,467
Hey!

590
01:00:02,533 --> 01:00:08,533
{\an8}THANK YOU FOR WATCHING CATCH THE GHOST

